  "texts": [
    "In our case we investigate such shifts with regard to the most significant terms associated with privacy policies before and after the regulatory regimes of the GDPR and CCPA became enforceable and the CPRA became effective.",
    "This required us to split our data into reference and target corpora at a specific point in time presumed to be a turning point in websites' decisions to adapt their privacy policies to regulatory change.",
    "Determining the turning point for this type of analysis is not trivial, as privacy policies might have changed several months before and after the enforcement dates of the respective laws.",
    "Previous work provides varying evidence of when websites started to adapt to new privacy legislation.",
    "For the GDPR, the points in time that saw the most changes in websites' privacy policies were found to be around the GDPR enforcement date in late May 2018 [4], one month before [15], and June 2018 [44]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For the GDPR, the points in time that saw the most changes in websites' privacy policies were found to be around the GDPR enforcement date in late May 2018 [4], one month before [15], and June 2018 [44]."
